                    }
                }
            }
            return new string(array);
        }
    }

You&#39;re calling `UpperCaseWords()` on `word` so it&#39;ll be looking for that method in the default `string` methods library (see &quot;Methods&quot; section of the sidebar in the [docs][1]).

Your method isn&#39;t extending the `string` class (adding your own method to `string`&#39;s library) and it&#39;s declared as `static`, so you can simply call it like this:


    var ProcessedOut =
        from word in ListOfWords
        let uppercaseString = UppercaseWords(word)
        select uppercaseString;

`static` means the method belongs to itself rather than a specific object instance so it can be called independently (as above), and in your case it&#39;s expecting a string as a parameter, so we give it `word`.

  [1]: https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/system.string?view=netframework-4.8

